Consider the following class:

```java
public class Point
{
    private int x;
    private int y;

    public Point(int x, int y)
    {
        this.x = x;
        this.y = y;
    }

    public void shift(int x)
    {
        this.x = this.x + x;
    }

    public int getX() { return x; }
}
```

What is printed by the following code?

```java
Point p = new Point(3, 4);
p.shift(10);
System.out.println(p.getX());
```

